{"title": "Take note of policy terms that don\u2019t cover some medical conditions", "tags": "business", "timestamp": "2024-01-06", "content": "Break a leg is a common way to wish others \u201cgood luck\u201d but it proved to be a sore point for a man here after being denied insurance when he suffered a fracture \u2013 in the wrong leg.\nSuch claims would usually be approved with no fuss by most private insurers, especially if the injury was caused in an accident. But this man\u2019s policy had a specific no-coverage term for his right leg as he had had knee replacement surgery."}